reviews.text: We went here for dinner on the evening of Lotus Lantern festival. At 45000 Kwon per person, the dinner set is slightly on the expensive end but you're mostly paying for the experience. For an all-vegetarian food, the quantity was more than sufficient. And the flavors were unbeatable. We were a little late post the lantern festival, so we only caught the last part of cultural dance - but it was worth it. If you can afford it, I'd definitely recommend checking this place out. The combination of the ambience, the food and the service will definitely leave an impression.

Atmosphere, food and cost all are good.

reviews.text: Very helpful staf, problematic mosquito and bugs, very noisy at night, we had trouble sleeping, definitely not a honeymoon destination for sure, good choice for trekkers as a starting point for Mt. Batur trekking

Two parts to separate: the tour (amazing) and rooms/villas (poor). The tour is excellent: 3:30 go up mountain, challenging walk, rewarding view and breakfast after. Guides are very good and will take you on extra tour if you can handle it. Better to arrange pickup from another hotel or city.

Many problems in the room: we immediately had to ask to fix the main locking door handle which was hanging off a nail, there were dangerous nails in the floor sticking out, and bottled water was initially missed in the room setup. The wifi works but is poor (could be due to the area). Room smells of mildew and the toilet of sewage (watch out, toilet is not connected to floor so it can tip over). Staff leaves light on inside room after cleaning (bad for bugs). No bug spray available by staff. No fridge in the room.

If you rent a scooter here please ensure horn and signal lights are working before payment. We got one scooter with poor engine and another with signal light & horn not working. Not safe! Also take pictures of scooter before you drive and before you are blamed for damage.

Taxi/driver arranged by this location drove too fast almost killing us, a dog, and someone on scooter - not impressed. This was not normal Balinese driving. DO NOT USE!

Staff is very friendly but reactive rather than proactive. They do not arrange laundry by the excellent place a few minutes down the road by scooter. Restaurant was ok for us and breakfast was actually fine/good. Breakfast choice should be more flexible. Our room accomodation was more quiet than other reviews we saw. Room temperature was ok in March. Welcome drink and towel arrangement was very nice but quickly the first impression did not last.
A perfect getaway and starting point of Mt. Batur trek

Very good place to stay. Though it is situated  5kms away from Ubud,  nice and peaceful place to stay. They have to increase the quality of Complimentary Breakfast they are providing. Other than that, a very good place to stay at Ubud. I recommend.
Great, cozy place. A bit noisy by the road, but worth it for the view.

reviews.text:
Awesome walk. Lots of scenery to see on the way. Rice fields local shops and restaurants. Be warned...food in the local restaurants take a long time to come to the table. Like a long time...i am guessing due to making it fresh to order for almost everything. Which is good but make sure you have enough time. 

Its quite hot and sunny so use suncream and a cap if you don't wanna get burned.

The ridge part itself was a lot shorter than i imaged, you can finish the walk in 15 minutes! And there is really only one part which gives you nice views. However if you keep walking on, you soon come to a small road which has spas and cafes along it.. but most of all it is surrounded by rice paddies which look amazing! We stopped at a cafe overlooking them and it was so peaceful!

Beautiful place but at entrance from the main road there is no indication. You must forget the path if you follow the Google map. Don't go down stairs from the main road's bridge toward the river. It will be serious for you. Maximum tourists do this error. You need to cross the 2nd. smaller bridge of the branch river. Actually the entrance of the Campuhan Ridge Walk is so typical. There are incomplete information on the Google map about the entrance.

Beautiful scenery and great exercise trail. Busy with people, we went an hour before sunset so it was much cooler. Not too difficult, has ups and downs so if you aren't in shape it could be a bit of a challenge. Best to go when it's not too hot / sunny as there's not much shade.

Just finished walking this trail, very pretty views & before sunset so it was cooler yet still that golden hour sunlight. Stone path the entire way but glad we had comfortable shoes. Bring a little bit of water. No bug bites. Took 30 minutes, free, definitely recommend!

reviews.text: Another picture perfect destination. The climate keeps changing here and so does the view. We were lucky that it didn't rain when we visited. Here too there is a botanical garden in the campus of the temple. The temple is situated inside the lake and is opened on special occasion. Entry to visitors is not allowed.

Nice little temple in the mountains. It has lovely little gardens to wonder through, all sorts of statues and mostly within context. There are some children's play equipment but it looked like it had been there 40 years. The lack of bullying shop keepers was refreshing and the experience was very relaxed compared to other tourist spots.

Temple and Balinese is inseparable and this  iconic Ulun Danu Beratan Temple is one of them. Located above natural lake on a highland, the air is fresh and cool~ 
Parking lot is huge. Cheap entrance ticket. Restrooms available but not so clean... many tourist, especially locals, can't keep it clean unfortunately. Souvenir stores available along exit route. Want to ride a boat? Or paddling by your self? It is also available, but I don't know how much it costs.
Just a tip, based on my experience the best time to visit the temple site is on weekday. Visiting on weekend or another holiday may cause you less comfortable because there are soooooo many people! 😄

The official opening time is much later. If you want to catch the sunrise, just walk in and speak to the guard. It's a pretty complex and the temple in the water looks beautiful. Unfortunately when I went there were a lot of clouds so we couldn't see the sunrise. Still managed to get some nice atmospheric shots.

This temple is one of the biggest must when visiting the island. The level of the water depends on the season but if you have the fortune to see it in a high level it can be a really beautiful symmetry to admire! The nature that surrounds the temple is also beautiful to photograph and there is a souvenir market at the entrance of the temple.

plus_code.compound_code: QWXR+3V Chiang Mai, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai, Thailand

reviews.text:
This hike is fantastic. The rewarding temple at the top is honestly what makes the whole experience worth it although the hike itself was nice.
It’s not overly difficult although I would absolutely recommend going in the morning (before 11) or late afternoon around 4pm. I went up at 2 and it was a scorcher! 

It is a bit tricky to find and I managed to ride up there fine on my rented scooter (you could walk from the main road but it seems unnecessary) but had some family who struggled translating it to a taxi driver so maybe keep in mind that it isn’t quite locally known as yet.

The walk was quiet and took about half an hour up. The trail is about 1.6km and I would say that it is easy with some moderate parts. I did it in summer in thongs (or flip flops or whatever you want to call them).

I would recommend this to anyone coming to Chiang Mai.

This is one of the best hikes or trail runs in Chiang Mai. The bottom section is over big rocks and then it comes to a temple and stream. You have to go up a very steep bank before the road. Cross the road then to the left you'll see where the trail continues. From here it's really nice and you just follow it all the way to the top. If you want to get into the temple for free, where the trail meets the road then right through some gates and up a concrete driveway. There you'll see signs up near the monks quarters pointing you in the right direction

The 45-minute hike to the temple was well worth it. The temple itself is beautiful and majestic, isolated in and amongst the beautiful backdrop of nature. There are on-going meditations, or so one of the signs says, so the only sounds you hear are of nature. A short trek from the temple grounds is the main road which you can call a taxi or grab from if all the exploring had left you spent. The trail to the temple is fairly well marked.
Excellent hike through the jungle. I’ve done this 5 times now. And it’s become a sort of spiritual/self development pilgrimage / reconnect to myself after staring at a laptop for days.... dooo it!

Beautiful trail full of nature and easy to walk. It takes around 30 minutes to get to the temple. You can take a bit more if you enjoy the walk and appreciate the sounds (birds, water, wind, etc).

If you see two roads just take the one of the right (always) and follow the sound of a small river.

The reward is a beautiful temple hidden in the mountains and sorrounded by nature.

Very entertaining show. Starts at 10:30.

It’s free to enter but you need to buy a drink (170 for beer, 250 for a cocktail). Bring some extra cash to tip the girls and take photos after.

Nice playback show with ladyboys. Some are well prepared and really beautiful other... should keep working. No entrance fee and no scam. You only have to buy a drink.
If you have an hour in the evening... go and visit it. Won't regret it.

If you visit Koh Tao you should ensure to drop by this location and watch their lady boy playback show. I highly recommend taking part in the Koh Tao Pub Crawl and going there as it's a big group then and prices are a lot cheaper.

There is free entrance but you have to buy a drink.
Good times and entertaining.  Worth a visit.

Drag show with gorgeous lady boys.  Paradise for heterosexuals looking for something to do. Too loud music.free entry but must buy a drink. About 200 bath. Worth visiting but bring ear plugs. Large crowd with appreciative clapping and  joining the singing. Emotional songs played. Recommended

reviews.text: This shrine is beautiful to see. Words cannot really describe it if I'm honest. It's worth going through the castle to see the shrine from there. Make sure you view the shrine with the tide both in and out - it's incredible on both occasions. Watch out for those deer! They're sleeping where you may not suspect and will try to eat your food.

It was really great! Beautiful island with these little deer you can pet. The Tori gate was amazing to see the only downside is how make tourist there actually was. We weren't able to get a picture of the gate on it's own when the tide was low. I definitely recommend it to foreigners it's a good bit of Japanese history but try to look up when it's not too busy.

This is almost in every tourist's bucket list visiting Japan. One of the most scenic spots. The shrine itself is built in the 12th century and the famous giant  orange colour Tori gate is right before it. If you visit during high tide you can see the Tori gate floating on water and during low tide, you can walk to the Tori gate. This is a very short boat ride from the shore and if you have a JR pass, the ferry ride is covered as well. There are lot of deer as well around the area. There are few good eating joints before the shrine.

Beautiful shrine sitting on the water. Lots of street food but be warned to walk around first as price can be different, especially for the local oysters. They are all good quality though as we tried a couple of shops. Must check tide time to see the floating shrine during high tide.
Wonderful place, so many deer around. Be carefull they will try to eat your bags and steal your food but they are so cute. Wonderful at low tide you can walk out. Highly recommend.

reviews.text: Second time eating here. The staff is friendly and well trained. Had the steak and burger. Both were excellent. Lovely setting outside having lunch on the lake under a huge tree. Will definitely return anytime I'm in Baccalar.

The atmosphere is amazing, beautiful outdoor seating with a dock that you can jump off into the lagoon.  The drinks are very good, but the food was average.  A little expensive, but you are paying for the location and atmosphere.

I had the hamburger, which was ordered medium, but came out well done.  The tuna steak was good, but I wouldn't order it again.  The watermelon vodka was one of the best drinks I've ever had.  The strawberry margherita was also very good.
It was such a beautiful place to eat and have relax. I recommend it at night it gets greater. I ask for shrimp and octopus. I also asked for a mojito and it was fantastic. Really recommend place.
Beautiful place by the lake. Awesome food and good service. prices are fine. You should definitely stop by for lunch or dinner if you’re in Bacalar

The ambiance is nice. The food is okay. The service is horrible. You have to find your own seat and pray that a waiter will acknowledge you to bring you menús. To order in this location is a challenge. It takes a long time to just get the drink orders going.  Food orders is another waiting game and even to get your check is a waiting game. Maybe hire more staff to attend guest. I went twice to give the benefit of the doubt that maybe my first time was bad luck. No. The second time there was hardly any people and the waiters seem to only entertain specific groups of people. Maybe the assumption that those people may tip them better. Who knows but it’s unfortunate. My experience was not pleasant. Once again. Location is Nice. Food is okay. Service is terrible.  as I waited I can feel my self aging.

reviews.text:
Very nice and careing manager.
It is within walking distance to the park entrance and the "strip". When you arrive with the local bus, the driver will drop you off directly at the hotel for 50 extra.
The food is good average.
As you are near the forest, I guess it is hard to avoid completely all insects especially ants in the bathroom. Beside this, the bathroom could have a little make over.
Bungalows are away from the street, so sleeping was good.

Good value for money altogether. Paid 700 baht for a private room. Room was clean,  spacious, and had a nice balcony.
Their restaurant is nice as well. Great location in town (right in the middle)
Would highly recommend for a one night budget stay, but not more (room is very basic)
Nice place to stay. Nice garden. Free bottle water. No problems.
Mr Khao Sok from green valley resort helpt us out when our travelagency left us alone. Great service! Also de room was super clean and tidy. Thumbs up!

Worst "Steak" ever. Looked good on the plate, but Slim like a French pancake, medium and soft like old shoe leather. Unfortunately it was also battered in pepper. The French fries you could count on your fingers. Thai food was much better but you will need a starter not to stay hungry

reviews.text:
Hands down, best Acai bowls on the island. 

Looking for a fresh coconut to drink? This is the place. 

Amazing fresh fruit and vegetable juices and cold brew coffees in a beautiful outdoor setting. The people who run this place are awesome as well. Don’t miss out!

This place looks small but when you get to the ordering window you see a large operation of people making juices and filling orders. We got excellent smoothies and shave ice, which had the texture of snow. A nice surprise from a place we just happened to pull into.

MUST STOP BREAKFAST ON THE SIDE THE ROAD! Sooooo yummy and healthy. My friends and I stopped by when they opened and it was some of the best açaí berry bowls I’ve had. Plus, they have terrific cold brew with homemade coconut cream 🤤🤤🤤

The best locally owned family spot in Kauai. Views of historic church & mountain are stunning, better the bowls & entire menu is off the charts amazing. Food is consistent, & always top notch. Great place for a short stop in on your way by.
Amazing fresh smoothie and fresh coconut. Friendly staff. Open air seating

You must try vietnamese coffee here. Very old style of a coffee shop, however this coffee shop is like an imagery of Dalat. Go here, order a “Ca phe phin” and ask anyone next to you about story of this coffee shop.

White (milk) coffee and yogurt are must try.

reviews.text: My husband and I have just finished building two modern homes.  one for ourselves and one is our guest house.  Looking for interior and exterior lights that create interest, found Clayworks Studio on-line.  After communicating with Chris to find out about the lights we decided to order. To our delight the sconces are well made and give such a warm and beautiful feel to our modern architecture. We chose black glaze for the exterior sconces and white for the interior sconces.  The glazes are beautiful! They arrived well packed and in beautiful condition.  Do not hesitate to plan to order these lights for your home.
Local company that has really fun and interesting pieces. Picking up in person was a breeze and was able to peek around in their cool studio!
Clayworks was great to work with. Very accommodating, friendly and flexible. We really enjoyed the process of working with them and love our sconces even more!

I got the chance to chat with the owner for awhile and he was a super nice guy.  Said he's been doing this for 30+ years.  The stuff they have in the store is awesome!  We got a couple of coasters and are hoping to someday buy one of the lamps they have.  They also had really cool plates.  Would recommend this if you are looking for something a little more unique and hand made.

I visited Clayworks for the first time last night for a reception titled, "The Great Grackle" that featured grackle themed art.  The variety of clay pieces for sale in the store varied from small whimsical pieces to larger pots for indoor/outdoor use.   The prices are reasonable and the staff is friendly and helpful.  I felt welcomed the moment I came into the door.

reviews.text: Very nice place to visit but take a few things into account. Very large place to walk around in so be prepared with sensible shoes. If you can walk around comfortably for an hour in cobbled stones in flip flops then carry on. There's very little shade having done this end of April so be smart in attire. Hats and sunscreen are a must. Also as your bottled water will boil, spring for a fancy water bottle that will keep your water cold.

We rode here from Hoi An by motorbike. The roads getting here weren’t too bad. We arrived late afternoon - around 15:30 and spent around an hour and a half here which was more than enough. It was really quiet which was nice.

There is a little bit of information about each structure so a self guided tour is fine unless you want a more in-depth experience.

There are about 3 Hindu temple ruins here. Hardly worth the drive and the entrance fee. For those who insist, there are some old temple ruins, a few brick structures that are still standing. Some recent reconstruction has been done, but it's unclear whether that enhances or detracts from the original structures.

In 2019, entry fee is 150K per person. Thankfully, the refreshment stands on site are very inexpensive. 

If this review was helpful, please click Like!

Cool place to see with what used to be awesome temples. Restoration is still ongoing on some of the sites. We went around mid day and it was pretty hot but nice and cool winds coming from time to time and not to crowded. One wonders why such a holy place would be bombed. You can see many of the bomb craters created from the carpet bombing of USA. On the way back there is also one cemetery of the Vietnames soldiers whom lost their lives in this horrible event.
Don't miss this place if you go to Vietnam. The site is cluster of Hindu temples in the jungle and it will bring you back in time. I was truly fascinated by it

plus_code.compound_code: X6RG+MX Banuang Daan, Coron Town Proper, Coron, Palawan, Philippines

reviews.text:
Hot but so good. I recommend visiting during the day as there will be less people so you could enjoy it more peacefully.

But if you want it a bit cooler (the air) then don't hesitate going in the evening. 

Definitely bring a bottle of cold water or any other beverage to keep yourself cool. As the spring is really hot and it's easy to get dizzy or even pass out.

Don't forget to take a walk around the spring as there's more than just the hot water spring.the view behind it is also amazing.

A little rough to get to get to passing through the town's and dirt roads but once you get here its pretty nice. The views and atmosphere was nice. The water was warm and soothing. I enjoyed my time spent here
Short stay but we had fun! The hotspring is so relaxing as expected 🤣🙌🏻 I would love to go back but longer stay so I can relax more.

the whole place is very clean. The hot spring was 40°C when we got there and dipping was no joke have to stay still until the body gets used to the heat before finally I could enjoy it but it was worth it and very relaxing.

Nice spot. However it would be great to have more options for little children. Toddlers should not bath in very hot water. Unfortunately there is not alternative for them (swimming pool or similar) and they have to wait and play outside the water. They should also provide showers.

reviews.text: Loved our breakfast here. It's a great beachfront restaurant to hang out. The prices are good. The fried rice and adobo tasted weird. It's too sour for my taste. If you're craving for pancakes, this is the place for you. The staff is super nice and helpful.

The catering service in this place is very good and very atmospheric. The staff is very polite and provides good service to the customers. We had a five-course meal, and all the food was great! The taste and setting are absolutely first class! Chef Omar visits us to check if everything is ok and if the food is delicious. I admire his skills and passion for food. This gives me and my boyfriend a perfect romantic dinner. We have such a wonderful night, everything is very good in the upper lira. The atmosphere, setting, service and dining are impeccable. Our dinner was part of a very cheap romantic combination, so we envisioned a main course and some others. The restaurant presented us with four exquisite dishes and bread. The staff is excellent and the chef personally talks to all the guests who are dining. This restaurant is highly recommended.
Went there after dinner for coffee and cakes. The cakes we had were absolutely delicious and yet inexpensive. Will definitely come back to try other items in the menu.
Unbelievable. Very lovely staff and amazing food and drinks. The wait for the food is about 20 mins and it says so on the menu. Definitely worth the wait.
Great selection of salads that you can customize it. Friendly service! Nice outdoors sitting area with view to the beach. Nice spa on site as well for an amazing massage after lunch!

reviews.text: Really enjoyed my stay here. Good location. Quiet atmosphere. The rooms were clean, large and very comfortable. 10/10. We paid about 500 THB per person for a Deluxe Double Bedroom.

The staff did not understand English at all.. None of the staff so that was a bit of a problem to communicate

Otherwise everything else was great be it the food, ambience of the place with such comfortable leather couches inside.. they also had seating arrangement outside by the water which added to the beauty of the place 

The food which were ordered was especially good and hot and spicy be it the spaghetti or the rice with basil or rice with chilly paste.. all the times were extremely spicy and that’s what I loved about the food here 

We really had a good time enjoying the food here and relaxing ourselves after a long day of tripping

We stayed in one of the 2 bed villas in September 2018, during the low season.

Although it met our primary need of having beds in separate, connecting rooms it was lacking in most other areas. It is in massive need of an update and is poorly maintained.

Each room has a large bathroom (unnecessarily big as the main rooms could have done with that space) Because they are partial outside, with no roof, the bathroom provides a constant supply of bugs (although doors can be closed)

The lake that the rooms look onto is pretty dirty and you can't go on your balcony without shoes because it is made of steel and is boiling hot during the day. 

We went into the onsite restaurant although it was 2 or 3 times the price of meals in Pai and the menu wasn't too appealing. It is also very far from town. We were OK as we had our own car but it would have been much more difficult without one as there are not many places to eat or drink nearby.

The pool was great though and is a lovely setting on quiet day. The staff were friendly and cleaned the rooms daily.

Looks nothing like the photographs. There's also no decent view. This is not a 4 star hotel. It's barely a 2 star with a balcony overlooking a tree in a ditch. The hotel is so far out from Pai and, whilst they offer a transfer, will charge you taxi rates. The room is big, though the shower is actually outside. Free parking is good, though it's on muddy grass so be careful not to get stuck. Avoid.

Relaxing cafe and instagrammable ;) 
Food is cheap & good.. Coconut shake 80B,  Fried chicken cake 80B, Caramel machiato 80B..

reviews.text:
Review (1). Food was amazing and cheap. All the staff were very helpful and friendly. Will definitely be going back again 😁😁😁

When I'm traveling I'm trying not to go to the same restaurant...I couldn't help here. Amazing staff, really really delicious food, especially breakfast and good coffee. This was my favourite place on the whole island.

reviews.text: Nice clean rooms and well maintained. Has nice garden and the ambience is great too. Rooms are Wooden small cabins that will fit you nicely. Friendly staff and good breakfast. 5 mins walk to the beach. Recommended place to stay.
Chalets like Rooms. Very good customer service   friendly staffs. On off seasons its extremely good. Near to beach. Loved it.

Sasvi is a great new place with modern cabanas. The wooden cabanas are very well designed and maintained and has all the modern facilities from AC, Fans,Hot water,dim Lights etc. There is a nice restaurant and a nice common area to relax. Owner Mr Sasi and the staff is really friendly and very helpful. There are lot of restaurants around Sasvi and the beach is just few mins away. Breakfast was good too. Can be recommended without any issue.

Awesome chalet like accommodation very close to Trincomalee town. Uppuveli beach is just around the corner, you can reach the beach by a 5 min walk from the Sasvi cabana. Place is very well maintained. Wooden chalets are very tidy clean and spacious enough for a couple. Bathrooms are also very clean. You have the AC in rooms , WiFi and hot water also. Garden is also well maintained and looks wonderful. Service is superb. Owner and the helping staff are really friendly and went the extra mile to make our stay memorable. We had the breakfast here and it was really good. Will visit again for sure. Highly recommended.
Very good place to stay.

reviews.text: We have had the most amazing stay. The staff as super friendly and the food is excellent. They were very helpful and always welcoming. Highly recommended!

Towards the expensive side. Food is awesome. Staffs, extremely friendly.

results.name: Elephant Orphanage - Pinnawala

plus_code.compound_code: 892P+9V Rambukkana, Sri Lanka

reviews.text:
Very nice place to visit. Specially for kids also for adults....... can closely watch elephants.
Best part is elephant bath at elephant bay. There are specific time frame for that. Any how nicest place to visit with family.

This was definitely an interesting experience. 
I've seen elephants before, but these looked different. We were sad to know that most of these elephants didn't have tusks because they have been tortured and their tusks were removed from them. I'm glad they're safe in the orphanage now. 
The most fascinating part for me, was watching them bathing in the river and enjoying the water.

The orphanage is located in Pinnawala town, near Kandy. It took us by car 2:30 hrs from Colombo.
The orphanage is huge and you can see loads of elephants in land being look after eating and walking. Then you can go to see them bath along the river and is just wonderful, check the times for the bath as I believe was 3 times. 
Breath taking to be in contact with these huge animals, kids can come close to them touch them and help to bath them a life time experience.

I have been to 3 different elephant places in SE Asia and i didn't enjoy how the elephants are forced to sleep in them confined tight spaces here. They also forced the elephants to walk through the village on chains every day. The elephant keepers have large metal spiked sticks and 1 of them was cowering from the keeper like it was terrified. Theres not much space for such a large animal to roam freely either. Its like they are in Prison!! The good thing is they get fed every day.

The most beautiful place. If you have visited you can gain much experiences with the elephants. The every single event happens is more colourful and makes are heart attractive to the elephants. I have gone pinnawala for several times and its a place to enjoy the life fullest with elephants.

reviews.text: The place has the chill and good vibes that I always look for when choosing a place to stay. The owners Greg (Filipino) and Thomas (French) were so accommodating and kind to us, we fell in love with the place right away! Would recommend this to anyone who wants to check out Nacpan Beach in El nido, Palawan, Philippines ❤

Home away from home. The owners, Greg and Thomas, were never short of warm hospitality and good food. The moment we arrived we felt like we joined a big family. The property is a short walking distance to Nacpan beach which makes it very convenient. Don't expect any 'privacy' since everything is communal. We were given the second level of their tree house, it's a small space with a bed and mosquito net, no outlets, no doors and walls -very raw and natural which is a pretty nice experience.

Amazing place, you must try.  It's cheapest accommodation in area wothvfull service.  The boss are nice boys and they give a lot information on the area.  Thanks Thomas and Greg.  J.

reviews.text:
Our whole trip in palawan (el nido and puerto prinsesa) was handled by Camarih last july 16
-21 2018. I will say that we had a wonderful and safe trip althrough out our journey. Drivers, tour guides, and receptionists was very kind that they ensure our safety throughout our journey especially that we had a lot of children and seniors. Eventhough we are a very big group (17 persons), they were able to handle all the tours safely and excitingly.. thank you camarih! I will definitely recommend this to others! Thumbs up!!!

Rubbish Company! On  january 07 of 2018 my husband and I took the van from the hotel Princesa Garden Palawan to El Nido. The company Camarih took us from the hotel with a large Van. After pick some people up in other hotels  they stopped the van  in a shopping center and changed for a small van, put a lot of people inside. I'm pregnant and they argumented with me to stay sit in the last sit of the van squashed. After so many complains and 40 minutes later they decided I was allowed to sit in the front sit beside the driver. So many people in the van had no spot for the bags, but they squashed  all the bags over my bag and in the end of the trip my bag was completely broken and opened. I talked with the driver who ignored me. My husband tried to contact the company so many times and they just told me they will not refund my bag that is not their responsability. I had to buy a new bag without refund for me is not a problem. But I will advise as much people I can against this company. Rubbish Rubbish Rubbish. The company Daytripper that I took today from El Nido to Puerto Princess airport so much better, no one problem and the driver very very friendly.

reviews.text: The other landing.. we ended up here in the midst of a festival, had a fantastic time though! Lots of local eats and drinks nearby.

The way to see Bristol harbour is from a boat and when we stay we tend to get either a carnet ticket or a three day- week pass to hop on and off the Bristol Ferry Boats. They also run Avon gorge tours so look out for special events. Staff are always lovely and helpful and will help the less able to board and disembark.
Great way to commute, more fun than Thames Clipper in London : )

So cool round trip experience with Number 7 boat trips (blue with shark in the bow). We could buy tickets inside the boat. They let us choose 40min round trip for £5 one way to hotwells (ss great britain, postcard bristol harbour view and Bristol Marina) OR Temple Meads rail station (the old town). No boring commentaries! They also offer us for £6 which is 1 more £, to go both sides of the harbour (the one we bough) hotwells and temple in an hour and 20minuts jumping to a different boat they've got, so we had doble boat experience (full round trip ticket it's also an all-day ticket!) We went early morning and we explored the Bristol Harbour, pubs, great views, food, locals... the cons were that they were running the timetibles Hotwells and Temple Meads A, so we had to keep on eye to be in the landings few minutes before the times showing in the boards to they see you, but they said in summer time or busy they run both... anyway was so much fun and great day! :D
Cheap and fast way of getting to the Templemeads station

reviews.text: This wonderful quirky Victorian Arcade was built in 1878. Its cast iron construction typical of Victorian practicality ...it houses little 20 shops, all of which reflect the surroundings, a little eccentric and quirky, with each strangely complimenting the other...it makes for an interesting shopping experience in the heart of Clifton
Always a great chilled out please plenty Toluca and nice things to do
Small but chic mini arcade with quirky shops to browse.
Quaint little arcade with the bohemian and artisan shops you would come to expect from Clifton.

Wow I loved this place. The Shops were so vintage, the floor was so beautifully laid. The staircase at the end was as if you were walking into a massive house. There were shops just on the righthand side open when we went. As a wheelchair user it was disappointing that the toilets were at the top too, but I think with it being an old property I didn't expect anything less. There was loads of room down the corridor between the shops.  All the staff in every shop were lovely but none of them beat the lady in the first shop called Jemima (the shop NOT the lady lol) was lovely. Nothing was too much trouble. She moved things so I could get through with my Wheelchair, she passed items down so I could have a look at them and even offered to order anything she hadn't got in stock and have it posted to my home address.

reviews.text: My favourite National Park and it's at my doorstep! Love teaching my kids everything I've learnt from years and years of visiting this place. Great 4wding, kid friendly beaches and great campsites. The only bad thing I can say is I've bent way too many tent pegs trying to peg the tent down when camping!

The facilities very good.
If your  walker you may find it excellent.

A beautiful National Park close to Port Lincoln.  Some great camping areas, some with drop toilets.  Entry fee payable at Port Lincoln Visitor centre or on-line.  Lovely beaches and vistas everywhere you look.  The waters are clear and inviting.
Realy good place. Book campsite online nice spots easy to reach the spots.

Excellent National Park with plenty of picturesque walks, a range of protected and secluded bays plus some very rugged coastline. The Sleaford - Wanna sand dunes were excellent along with Memory Cove. Plenty of beaches and rock pools to explore also. We will definitely be back to camp again.

reviews.text: An older building in a great Nimman location, located by Soi 8, a busy and vibrant neighborhood. Dozens of restaurants and bars are within a 1-block radius, hundreds within a 0.5km radius. There is a large 24-hour 7-eleven on the ground floor with two separate halves, a pretty interesting setup. There are a lot of different rooms available for rent in the building for short- or long-term stay. Some rooms are recently renovated and quite fancy, others are a bit older, all depending on price. (This is why the reviews are mixed here on Google Maps.) I’ve been in the building 6 months and love it here. Location, location, location! Here’s a photo of my view (180-degree city view).
Armo Nimman here in this building

It is an older building, so don't expect anything that will blow your mind. I stayed in an older room with updates furniture, but I know there are completely remodeled rooms. The person I rented from was an absolute peach. I LOVED having a 7-11 downstairs. It's 24 hour magic was necessary for when I caught a cold. It is on the busiest street in the city, so don't expect to cross into the neighborhood next door (with all the best food and shops) without some work. Everything you could need is within walking distance. Overall this place was a perfect introduction to Chiang Mai. Did I mention I could see the mountains from my room? So beautiful.
Great location and spacious and clean room. Very satisfied.
Location is great, limited car park a bit old inside.

reviews.text: A very nice interior and a pleasant cold in the middle of a hot summer.

This place is awesome. This is the Airbnb "dream," you get a huge loft apartment in downtown florence with a bathtub next to the bed, huge fireplace on the first floor. Working kitchen. More closets then you probably have at home.
Location is perfect.
Florence is amazing, the folks at Crete dei neri make it extra. You feel like you are renting an apartment from a cousin, and it is all paid and they only want to make you happy. We needed to leave our bags and they said: just keep the place for the rest of the day, no problem...  they make the policy and it is exactly something that family would do. 
We were trying to do an amazing honeymoon from nyc to Italy for a week and this was the cherry on top.  You should consider staying longer and using it as the jump pad for all your tuscany adventures.
Don't rent a car in Italy unless you have parking, take the train and rent a scooter at a respectable place if you know what you are doing. You will save less and get to sleep more.
Corte is the place, spend the extra money on a nicer room and you get a lot more bang for your buck...
Fantastic.
This place is amazing. It has a very nice feel towards the rooms. The location is really nice. The owner gave us a full tour on a map of where everything is and what he recommends.

1- Excellent b&b staying. The room is big with classic decor that gives u the feeling of old hysterical city.
2- The room was clean .
3- The bathroom was clean and has a lot of space.
4- The room is equipped with mini bar, safety box and an air conditioning.
5-The staff is very friendly and helpful.
6- The location is near everything.

Adorable B&B exquisitely decorated with old world charm and modern conveniences. Situated right in the heart of Florence so you can easily get to all the amazing sites in less than 10 minutes by foot. The owner and staff are so helpful and caring and genuine. I will be back and will miss my beautiful temporary home!!

reviews.text: You have to see that at least one time in your life. This is our incredible planet! Then you seating on the edge of the crater you can feel the breathing of the Earth. Very important to go with a good guide in good time. So you can enjoy the beauty of this place and get good photos.

Cool place to catch the morning light...

Do prepare for the journey; might be challenging for some (due to poor road conditions)...

Amazing view and scene once you reached the top...
Epic moment..
Got a very outstanding and unforgettable experience for being on Bromo. The beautiful nature and views surround this active volcano really gives you thought on how beautiful the mother-nature is

We've visited the Bromo volcano and the surrounding park on a damp morning. It was still misty when we reached the top but cleared on the way down. Do make sure you are able to walk stairs since the last part of the trip consisted of steep stairs towards the rim of the vulcano. Unless you are afraid of heights, you can even make a round trip around the rim.

Well worth the experience of getting up early to see the sunrise and walking across the sands to climb up to view the active volcano. A great experience for the young and old. Mount Bromo can be an easy or hard a hike, rugged or as touristy as you want it to be. The view is spectacular, just get there early to secure a good spot. Also bundle up, it gets pretty cold at the top especially early in the morning. However, do wear layers as it gets quite warm when you're approaching the crater. The crater itself is crowded, and in my opinion, lacking a few safety measures. However, it's breathtaking and truly a cool place to see.

reviews.text: A short motorbike ride is require to get to the entrance of the waterfall. Fr there the walk in is about 1km on flat terrain. The waterfall here was tall! We did not expect the view to be great, so it came as a surprise. U’ll definitely get really wet trying to capture all the nice shots.

Really breathtaking! Though be ready to get wet as you need to walk under the water fall. Best would be to carry rain gear and also some protective casing for phone,wallet,etc. You will reach the carpark after which some local guides will take you to the falls by bike. After the bike ride, there is a ~2km walk to the falls. Also ensure you're wearing slippers. There are locals selling slippers and ponchos outside. They will definitely try to charge foreigners a higher price so beware!

First off - probably the most spectacular natural scenery I’ve ever seen.  If you are in East Java, do not miss this.  I’ll let pictures speak for themselves, but the important part of the review is getting there.
The walk to the waterfall parking is about 4km, you can rent a scooter / driver but it’s a bit sketchy (I paid 250,000 RUP).  I didn’t have any issues, but there were a few close calls.  So if it sounds like you might not like it, just walk.  Small entrance fee at parking area, then another 2km walk, a bit slippery so have decent sandals though I would recommend hiking shoes you’re willing to get wet.  They sell ponchos or bring a rain coat.  You will get wet, but it will be worth it.  There’s a number of falls, the last being the best.  You’ll have to wade through knee deep water at times and will get rained on.  To get to the last fall, there’s a bit of a climb over some rocks, not too bad for most people.  You can swim at the last fall, I did not but others were.  That’s about what you need to know.

This is very high waterfall and beautiful waterfall, if you go here you must have a raincoat. you can go to this waterfall by a car or a motorcycle. you will find a lot of vegetation and animal in here. but keeps the place clean.
Stunning!! You will get wet so bring some dry clothes, and the $2 waterproof phone bag is absolutely worth it to get some fantastic photos! Great experience :)

reviews.text: Free thermal baths. Come with your own towels, bring snacks and enjoy mineral water. Picnic area near by and good location for a stroll.
Wonderful. Free mineral bath!

Come tutte le terme libere, questo posto fa sperare che l essere umano si possa gestire senza un cambio col denaro. E in effetti durante il giorno è così. Vasche pulite, calde e persone cordiali. La sera invece, alcune persone arrivano a parcheggiare le auto a filo delle vasche e non hanno nemmeno l accortezza di recuperare la loro immondizia. Giustificate le multe per chi accede al parco in auto.il posto è meraviglioso e va preservato non perché è gratuito ma perché molti credono che lo possa essere.

Esperienza da fare!! Acqua a 42° nelle due vasche. La più grande è anche un po' più profonda e con i sassi al suolo, l'altra ha lastre a terra che ricoperte di una patina di alga risulta più scivolosa. La vasca coperta all'inizio del percorso pedonale ha un acqua meno calda, poco sopra i 30°.

Vasche di pietra con acqua calda circondati dalla natura e con la bellissima panoramica. Un spazio in mezzo alla campagna, sole, cello, acqua all'aria aperta e bella gente. Davvero, proprio così.. Portate qui il necessario e accendete il vostro fuoco! 🌺🌺🌺

reviews.text: I’ve been in Florence for 3 days & have had exceptional dining experiences: this place was so awful, I left without finishing my dinner or wine. I ordered risotto with asparagus & vegetables. I was presented with a plate of nonsense about 5 minutes after I placed my order. Did I receive risotto? No. I received a plate of rice, with asparagus that was so over cooked, it had the consistency of baby food. I’m not exaggerating. It’s takes a lot for me to pick up & leave but I thought to myself, “Absolutely not. Im not letting this happen in this enchanting city.” This is the equivalent of an NYC tourist trap in Times Square. Don’t do it. Just don’t!

This is Florence. The atmosphere was warm and homey, the wait staff was kind and proficient, but the rock star is the menu. This is where Florentines go to eat. Reasonably priced and worth the wait. Open for lunch, too. Highly recommended!!! 😋😊❤️
Great little local place. Service was best I've had in Italy.

This is a good restaurant, with yummy, local food - it's very good but not amazing. We ordered lasagna and beef stew - the beef stew was delicious! We saw several reviews mentioning the lasagna, and it was good, but not "the best I've ever had". Although it was busy, we got a table without a reservation and had great service. It is reasonably priced.

Small, but food is good! Specially near the center all too expansive,but here is okay!
(Lunch time almost local people go there to eat lunch!)

reviews.text: The Sassi is the old town of Matera and it is definitely worth a visit. I would suggest spending one day in this area so you have time to walk around this landmark and European culture capital. In between the old houses you will find museums as well as small places for coffee, cake and pasta.

An amazing place. Stroll the narrow streets and soak up the atmosphere.  It is a UNESCO  site and European city of culture this year. So much to see. Visit if you can soon before it becomes more congested with tourists.
Amazing town you have to see. Just find yourself a good map, it is a labyrinth of stairs. Really impressive and breathtaking.

What an amazing early spring weekend in April. Definitely the time to come to visit before the Summer heat and what I imagine would be the massive crowds this year, the year of culture as Matera is Euro City  of Culture 2019. 
If you visit there are plenty of good restaurants to choose, but booking is advisable with the busiest.
Finally, make sure you have really good grippy footwear as anywhere off the level streets and the Sassi steps are seriously slippy and possibly in the wet could be so dangerous for the less sure footed.
Enjoy Matera, it is Fabulous!!!

It wasn't the best weather. The sun was covered by tons of clouds 
We couldn't open our eyes to take nice pictures. 
However it's really a worth to go place. 
All around full of stones 
Surrounded by stones
Nice view. Just couldn't find a great place to park. Had to go very far away and walk the whole way to Matera

Da svariati anni il mio punto di riferimento per la cucina cinese. Locale elegante, pulito, e senza gli odori che spesso caratterizzano questi locali. Oltre alle sale interne vi è anche un gazebo con tavoli all'esterno. Vario e ottimo il menu cinese, porzioni abbondanti. Più dì recente si è aggiunta l'offerta del sushi (preparato a vista), anche questo promosso a pieni voti. Titolari e personale sempre gentili e disponibili. Prezzi contenuti. Cinque stelle meritate.

In questo ristorante...si mangia la cucina cinese buona e prezzi nella norma da alcuni anni si può mangiare il sushi...il locale è ben curato e pulito.  Non ci sono odori che a volte restano sui vestiti. Un buon locale.

The incredibly delicious wine is made by them, from the surrounding vineyards.
You can enjoy the pool, relax in the spa and even spend the night in a cosy room.
We've spent three days and two nights there and it has been perfect.

Замечательное место, прекрасный вид на побережье, безупречный сервис, отличная чистота и не менее изысканная и выдающаяся еда. Справедливые цены (полное меню 39, меню без второго 30). Я очень рекомендую посетить этот ресторан
Incredibile paesaggio con vista mare da un lato è collina dall'altro e una cucina sublime squisita deliziosa

Posto stupendo, vista incantevole sulla costa , servizio impeccabile, estrema pulizia e non ultimo cibo ricercato ed eccezionale. Prezzi giusti  (menu completo 39, menu senza secondo 30). Lo consiglio moltissimo forse più a pranzo che a cena per poter godere della vista dalle tante vetrate sulle quali si affacciano i tavoli. Ho mangiato li fuori stagione ed il menu per pranzo era fisso ma con molta disponibilità a personalizzarlo per le esigenze dei vari ospiti. Bravi!

Abbiamo ancora scelto il Dea Flora!!! Domenica scorsa abbiamo festeggiato la cresima di nostra figlia Giorgia ed è stata una magnifica giornata.  Dopo che ci siamo trovati benissimo nelle precedenti occasioni di festa della famiglia non avevamo dubbi ed anche stavolta è stato un successo. Il posto è incantevole, la cucina è raffinata e l'ospitalità senza eguali. E' sempre un sentirsi a casa in un ambiente incantevole con un panorama mozzafiato che scalda il cuore. Consiglio il Dea Flora a  tutti quelli che vogliono conservare un ricordo speciale di un giorno importante. Laura

reviews.text:
This is the best zoo I’ve ever see in the world, you’ll see infinite kind of animal and free, not in cages, you’ll be able to get very close with lions, tigers, zebras, elephants, giraffes and every animal you can think.
You can spend a whole day within the zoo and theme park, there are also many restaurants for all range of spend.
I really suggest to go there at least once in your lifetime!!!

Very lovely park with a lot of different animal species. But quite pricey and terrible logistics which cause massive traffic jams while on the safari. Their solution is to take the animals away from the car trail, which in our case led us to queue over an hour in our car to feed the giraffes for nothing. By the time we got there all animals were taken away.
Me, my wife and some friends were there for about 5 hours but I must say that we had a wonderful time. I would definitely recommend it.
Cool experience. Make sure to ration your vegetables and maybe pick some up before you arrive.  Also don't bring a car you care about getting scratched up.

This is a fantastic family day trip plan. The animals are friendly and come up to the cars. Go early because mid day it seems to get busier. It is a drivethrough safari staying in the car. There is also an amusement park seperately that you can visit.

reviews.text: High standard. Modern hotel. I had to wait for the owner for over 20 minutes. The welcome was not pleasant.
very helpful staff. clean accomodation and very central to the city
Roof top apartament awesome

Ottima struttura recentemente restaurata con stanze molto spaziose e confortevoli nei servizi (tv, clima ecc.). Il bagno completo di una fantastica doccia, al centro di Polignano e comodissima come logistica. Meritevole.

La struttura è raggiungibile in auto solo al mattino visto che nel pomeriggio l’area diventa ztl; comunque anche al mattino è impossibile trovare un parcheggio nei pressi del B&B.
La struttura non è dotata di ascensore.
La nostra camera era molto bella anche se molto calda e, a causa della disposizione degli interni, di difficile areazione.
Altra nota negativa, in camera c’erano delle formiche che in parte entravano dal balcone.
Il servizio navetta per la spiaggia non è assolutamente efficiente; le corse programmate sono sempre in ritardo, spesso il tragitto viene modificato senza preavviso e a volte la navetta non passa proprio, lasciando le persone a piedi.
Al momento del check-in viene richiesto il saldo del soggiorno in anticipo, cosa abbastanza inusuale.
Personalmente non tornerei e sconsiglio a chiunque di soggiornare in questa struttura.
Del resto, a Polignano, ci sono molte valide alternative.

reviews.text: Amazing piece of work up on the edge of the cliffs. Worth the sweet hiking up! Great panoramic views.
It is an interesting journey through one of the oldest independent countries in Europe. The castle has a nice view with many spots to be explored.

The Castle and Tower themselves are small, but for the price it's a nice way to spend an hour or two. The views from the Tower - IF you can climb it- are spectacular. The gardens are lovely. And the small museum is very informative about San Marino' s history. I definitely recommend making the effort to walk through if you're here. Just beware that to climb the Tower itself, you must go up a ladder where at the top there are metal wire steps (rebar) and a tight-ish space to squeeze through. Definitely not safe for kids.
Nice View from top Tower-You can walk from first to last Tower without living Top-google suggest otherwise
San Marino is a great place to visit, friendly people, interesting places to see and great prices. perfume, alcohol, tobacco are hard to beat.

reviews.text: We celebrate my best friend wedding here. The food is amazing as the location is stunning. Deinitely worth a visit.
Top
Fantastic!!!

Cibo di  ottima qualità. Infatti per anni sta vincendo le stelle Michelin.
Posto tranquillo e paesaggistico.  Ottimo  per  cerimonie.
Proprietari gentilissimi e si vede che fanno il loro lavoro con passione.

Buonasera, sono stato al Ristorante stellato Le Trabe Tenuta Capodifiume domenica 24 febbraio 2019 a pranzo, sono appositamente arrivato dalla Calabria, poiché volevo davvero testare se le foto sul sito rendessero veramente l'idea. Bhé, a dire il vero, non rendono molto l'idea, poiché dal vivo la rendono molto di piú ed è molto, ma molto meglio...INCANTEVOLE...consiglio a tutti di andare. Arrivato sul posto, ho trovato un'atmosfera bellissima, un posto di altri tempi immerso nella natura, personale squisito, location meravigliosa e piatti favolosi. Complimenti allo Chef Marco Rispo. Ascoltate le mie parole...andate e rimarrete felicemente sorpresi...complimenti a tutto il personale del Ristorante.

reviews.text: Excellent choice of wines both local and national. Food has a twist, pasta is excellent. Staff very friendly and restaurant was full on a Monday night with both tourists and locals. View not the best. But definitely worth a visit. Also cheaper than Positano.

My favorite restaurant in all of Positano! The staff are so sweet and make you feel like family! I was here for my honeymoon and ate here several times, attempting to eat everything on the menu. From pizza to fish to dessert, nothing disappoints. Can’t wait to return. Grazie!!

AMAZING! 
Thank you Giuseppe for the wonderful hospitality and kind gestures for our evening in your restaurant.
I sent a message on the restaurants Facebook page and Giuseppe was kind and happy to help with any questions.
We were celebrating a birthday, and as soon as we walked into the restaurant they congratulated us with happy birthday wishes and were so nice :)
The restaurant is cosy and just lovely to be in.
The food was absolutely delicious, we felt full but couldn't stop eating.
Everything was fresh and made on point, beautifully presented as well.
We will definitely come back next time!

Amazing service, made us feel like we were special even though we showed up in hiking shorts!! The food was also amazing, highly recommend this restaurant the food was amazing and the desert blew us away! Had the mini canolis and the riccotta cheese tart.

The establishment is very astetiy pleasing and comfortable, also the food was awesome. Somehow my 4 course taste meal turned into 6 courses! It was all delicious, the lamb in particular was like butter.

reviews.text:
It is much more smaller than Pompeii but the building's are more preserved. You don't need to spend a whole day to see it and you can perfectly combine it with the trip to Vesuvius.
Like in Pompeii so here as well you'll be able to travel back in time in your imagination...

It seems tiny in comparison to Pompeii, but you can still spend a lot of time here exploring every nook and cranny, especially if you get the audio guide. I do recommend the audio guide but it has a ton of material so I skipped many of the entries. Even still I was there for 3-4 hours and had a great time. My only problem was several areas were closed and the audio guide wanted us to visit them, so that was very disappointing. There was one very cool area we missed out in because it was closed. I do understand the closures at a place like this but really wish there was some notification or something. Not sure how long these things will be closed but I think I would recommend going to Pompeii instead and get a guided tour of some sort.

There is a gift shop here with some interesting items at okay prices. They accept cards for the entrance tickets. They have free bathrooms here. We didn't see any food inside, but a few minutes outside the area there are many restaurants.
If at all possible you should spend some time there. Amazing artifacts, beautiful mosaic tile still intact. A guided tour would be best.

Definitely worth the visit even a little bit farther away. Area is not too big to wonder around, you can see enough in two hours. First the ruins and then the museum and the boat exhibition.

Be sure not to miss the skeletons when lowering down to the moat before leaving the ruins area.

We visited during museum week which gave the entrance for free. Thank you very much!

An excellent, well preserved archaeology site. Opted to access the site by train which was easy (straight walk down the hill). Less busy compared to Pompeii but also a smaller site, you can go round the whole site in half a day. The audio guide was also great to have (picked up after entering the site).

reviews.text: Absolute great location and good service! Nice view and when the windows are open you feel like sitting outside. Good selection for Breakfast and dinner. Might be worth to enlarge the variety of Ice cream flavours with the summer approaching. When we were there (on Easter weekend) the only choice was Vanilla or Banana. Both of them were excellent but might have taken more if more options would have been available!
It's cool that you can have a great view while you take a coffee. And the sounding is full of pretty flowers in this season.💕
Great tastes combined with relaxing atmosphere and a breathtaking view to the city of Graz!

Loved the experience and food. It's truly magical in winter and the evening. The atmosphere was cosy, the food tasted great, and the service was wonderful. I highly recommend this place for dinner the view and lights are just spectacular.

The food was amazing !
The environment excellent!

reviews.text:
The sashimi station is very small (You can see from gallery). You may have to wait forever because they rarely care to refill it. The buffet period is just one hour. Within our meal they refill only two times and those two times we have to ask them to refill.

They should discard sashimi  from their menu and ads if they don't want their customer to eat. 

In overall, this restaurant is quite expensive comparing to the price you pay for the lower quality of food. 

Don't expect too much. I recommend you to try other restaurant when you visit Bana hills.
The kids like the sushi. And the pineapple salad dressing is nice.

Food was mediocre and sometimes incorrectly labeled (see picture). Waitinf staff don't seem to be working at all (see picture) and don't even bother to put napkins on tables when guests come. Overall, this restaurant needs better management.
Good Food, fast cleanup.

The sushi here isn't like sushi at the hotels, it was quite good. Unlike most buffets that feature sushi, this place has smaller amounts of rice in the nigiri so it feels like you are getting good value. I would eat sushi here over 90% of the places in the country. 

They also have an udon bar, some Korean spicy rice cake, decent french fries, and the tonkatsu was really well done (deep fried pork cutlet with panko). All of my American friends enjoyed the place and found things they liked.

reviews.text: Fun time tasting their good wines with explanations on the process and varietals used. Also taken through the olive oil and lavender production processes.

This is UNESCO World heritage protected site as one of the rare examples of intact agricultural landscape made by Greek colonists when they took this beautiful bay from local population. I would like more investment but even like this is it perfect place for bike or walking tour. You can reach it from Stari Grad and it stretches almost to neighboring beautiful small towns of Jelsa and Vrboska. In spring you can find nice asparagus here. And try to avoid high summer as it can be really hot here if you are not near sea.
Nice beach
Zato što je Polje isprepleteno poviješču, poljoprivredom i kulturom. To je prepoznao i UNESCO

Starogradsko polje, plodna velika ravnica u središnjem dijelu otoka Hvara, kulturni je krajolik upisan na Listu svjetske baštine UNESCO-a. Sedmi je hrvatski lokalitet upisan na Listu, 2008.godine. Njegovu geometrijsku strukturu zadali su grčki kolonisti IV. stoljeća prije Krista podijelivši polje na jednake parcele. U polju se nalazi 73 pravokutnih parcela omeđenim suhozidima te sadrži više od stotinu arheoloških lokaliteta.

plus_code.compound_code: 7JVR+9C Kandy, Sri Lanka

reviews.text:
#kandy #SriLanka
The Octagon aka Paththirippuwa is one of most important buildings in Dalada Maligawa. It was built in 1802 AD by King Sri Wickrama Rajashinghe, the last king of the Nayakkar Lineage. It's name derived from the tamil language. It means 'To see while seat'. In 1998, LTTE attacked the Sri Dalada Maligawa and the Octagon also being damaged. It has been restored after that scene and it took one year to restore the building.
An iconic part of the temple of tooth. Said to be the king's stage for addressing citizens.
Very creative place build by kandyan kings
Great and beautiful place in Dalada Maligawa. Some Presidents give their oath here.

It was a well known fact that the paththirippuwa , which had been considered as the symbol of identity of the of the Kandyan Architecture was built in 1802 A.D on the instructions of kings Sri Wickrama Rajasinhe., who was the last king of Nayakkar Lineage (1798-1815 A.D). The name derived from the Tamil Language, meant as the place of this great construction was a master craftsman named Devendra Moolacharya. Out of his construction Magul Maduwa or the pavilion held a prominent place.

According to tradition he had born in Matale, was staying for some time in Kotmale and finally lived in Handessa, till his tragic death which had taken place as a suicide for feeling ashamed of losing one of his fingers on the orders of king, who listened to slander against this great craftsman. This building a master piece of Kandyan Architecture was octagonal in shape and the roof was an attractive creation with a steep gradient.

During the bomb blast by the LTTE terrorist on 25th of January 1998 A.D, aimed to destroy the Buddhist Heritage the paththirippuwa too faced damage. It was pleasure to see the reconstruction of the building. The patronage of the Minister in charge of the Harbor should be appreciated. Concrete mortar and plaster were pumped to the cracked and vibrated walls through novel technological methods to strengthen the building. Reconstruction work had in no way obstructed strength of the ancient building and it had been a great pleasure too. - sridaladamaligawa.lk

reviews.text: This was a pretty special spot. Baby seals playing in the waterfall until they are big enough to hit the coast. The drive itself is pretty spectacular and worth it, if it's open.

Its a shame that it's permanently closed! This was one of the best experience I had in Kaikora, and unbelievable close up encounters with baby seals. Hope the roads and steams will be restored someday so everyone else gets a chance to learn about them and understand the importance of wildlife conservation.
Found by accident , utterly amazing!

One of the Highlights of New Zealand.... Though I hear it might be gone due to earthquakes... Baby seals head inland to a waterfall where they live till their old enough to head out to sea... Very Cool. Spent half the day hanging out with these little guys. Free and definitely worth a visit.

A perfect location for seal pups. The walkway is best visited in the colder months. Its a very short walk and certainly worth the stop! Playful seal pups abound.. please respect them and their environment for them to continue living in this beautiful space.

results.formatted_address: 3170950, Gibbston 9371, New Zealand
results.name: Nevis Bungy & Swing

plus_code.compound_code: W2PH+VH Gibbston, Otago, New Zealand

reviews.text: Must do for adrenaline junkies. Free pick up and drop off from town. Takes Upto 3-4 hours . Great value for money deals if decide to do second jump on the day. Best Is the trilogy option of Bungy Swing and Catapult.

Did the catapult and loved it. It is over in a matter of 45-60 seconds so bear that in mind when you book. The catapult Is right next to the Nevis swing so got to watch my fellow adrenaline seekers drop 146m before swinging and I wish I also did it. It’s worth noting if you’re trying to decide whether or not to do one, two or three activities, all I’ll say is don’t just do one (money pending). Once you’ve done one you’ll be pumped and want to do the other so better to pay for a package and get a little bit of a discount. I wish I did two as they are what you would consider once in a lifetime opportunities.

Had the swing here and it's super thrilled to do. The operator always surprises you so don't even bother to answer their questions. It's a good surprise though. You can handheld your own camera or GoPro when doing the swing. Very fun and exciting experience. Definitely recommend it for all the adrenaline seeker. Suitable for all!
Did the Nevis Bungy. It was great! Overall they got it all figured out here well - great service experience. Would definitely do it again.

I went to watch my husband do the bungy and the staff was AMAZING! They were double and triple checking everything, very upbeat, fun and chatty. I felt like I could have just hung out there all day! They are great at getting you pumped up for the big jump! The photos and video you can buy after was definitely worth it and no editing needed, it is social media ready! And cant forget the bus driver!! He was hilarious, cracking jokes all the way there definitely lightened the mood!

reviews.text:
Great ski resort in winter with broad, long slopes and modern lifts. You will find slopes of low up to Olympic difficulty (Streif)! 

It's very famous in Europe so expect lots of tourists during weekends, holidays and international skiing championships.
The best snowboard resort I've ever been: cabin and windshield lifts, amazing views and affordable prices

I love to ski in Austria and what a better place to go then to Kitzbuhel. I love it their so many slopes eill never get bored from diffrent levels of slopes available. Very good resort for familys too with lots of diffrent laugage available for kids to learn how to ski. I cant wait to go again!!

Worse place for snowboarding ever. Compared to other nearby resorts: crowded, limited and expensive parking (it's free elsewhere!) and full of long and flat traverses that even the lightest breeze make impassable on a board. Plus the worse invention ever: a heated chairlift!?!. This makes your bottom hot and wet. Skiing clothes are designed to keep you warm inside, while the outside can stay cold and therefore dry. This heated seat is just so stupid. Don't waste your time coming here, there are much better places.
I love nature, views and cleanness. Here Ive got it all. One of the most spectacular view Ive ever seen.

reviews.text: Really good walk in the evening, and then the day it will be very bustling. Also, have a look at the basement for great food. And ATM's.

Marina Bay Link mall is one of those establishments in Singapore that helps both professional and visitors to appreciate the beauty of the city. Attended a buyer workshop here together with my boss and one would see people from different walks of life conducting their business meetings as well. The executive room that we had was very spacious and cosy. They even have free coffee and teas as complementary drinks during our meeting. Not to forget that there's a lot of restaurants down the building that is splendid to do after a very long and tiring meeting. Should you be in Singapore one of these days, don't forget to drop by here.

Very low end management. The staff was not trained to explain their parking promotion and told shoppers like me that 4 hrs of free parking with $30 spend. But didnt say this does not apply to weekday where it is 30 mins parking only. Resulting in $24 parking fee which mall refuse to refund
cozy but wonderful place to visit , shop , dine & entertain kids
You'll find great stuff there! Love the home and office store!

reviews.text: The bowls are incredibly tasty , we came every day since the day we discovered the place . We had a Maverick for breakfast every morning and it’s truly delicious . It’s true that is a little bit expensive but I don’t agree with a lot of the other bad reviews . Smoothie bowls have to be cold cause if not when you’re at the middle of it , it’s warm and taste like a soup. I tried smoothie bowls in a lot of different places and none can get even closer to this ones . I really recommend it . Amazing job guys.

I love the food and the location. Could eat their everyday. Probably a bit pricey especially for Bali standards. But the quality is also better than at the most places. I prefer the Nalu bowls store on the Bukit. The one in Canggu is really small and crowded. Finding a parking space there is also challenging.
I was a bit disappointed about the small size of the bowl but omg finally someone gets the açai bowl texture right

Nice place to chill, near to rice fields so u can enjoy the nature in Bali, its near to the city. Its located right beside NOOK bali cafe. Instagrammable place to take pictures. For the food, it is fresh, love the coconut flakes and the smoothie bowl is refreshing

Nalu Bowls had a nice chilled atmosphere but the bowls were unimpressive sadly. Taste was okay. Granola and coconut flakes were stale and toppings weren’t generous - our food was underwhelming for the steep price.

results.name: Pondok Sawah Asri

plus_code.compound_code: F7Q2+XX Ubud, Gianyar, Bali, Indonesia

reviews.text: Absolutely amazing authentic place to stay.  Place is located a small distance away in a quiet location but very accessible to ubud centre. Asri the host is amazing cooked us tasty breakfast and dinner and service was second to none. The villa is spotless and if you are looking for a authentic Balanise experience this is your place. The hosts are amazing the place is amazing only wish we had found it earlier.
Amazing villa and lovely family. Definitely recommend staying here.

Imagine having your own superb villa in the middle of a village in Ubud. Pondok Sawah Asri is located in a small village just off Jalan Penestanan yet is still has easy access to mini marts, supermarkets, restaurants, cafes and laundries. The villa has daily breakfast, daily housekeeping, wifi, air con, wifi, a lovely pool and a truly beautiful garden. This has been my favourite place to stay in Ubud and being in the midst of traditional Bali village life is wonderful! Wayan and Asri are wonderfully warm and friendly hosts and I cannot recommend this place more strongly!

Clean, nice appearance. Built in the middle of a rice field.  Lots of little critters everywhere (frogs, bats and mosquitoes). There was an issue with hot water.  Turning the nozzle either right or left the water was cold, called the owners they said to wait for the hot water heater to heat up or to "turn the nozzle the other way" lol.  I spent some time and found that there is one specific spot when the knob is turned slightly to the right that has hot water... Very aggrevating.  There's a big bathtub, but there isn't enough hot water to fill it up.   The owners were really friendly and kind. Nice spot for pictures, but I learned that hotels are more suitable for me.

What a great place with wonderful owners! Very calm location in the rice paddies, nice warungs nearby. And Ubud centre not to far off by car or scooter (or about 20min walk)
Wayan and Asri are both great, friendly and caring people.
